    <item>
      <title>Weekly Question:  11-7</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=26107#M26107</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We were told in an earlier weekly question that there should be some right click imbue aggro proc clickies in TSS.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; None have been found yet, and ok, if they're embedded into content we've not found yet, ok.. no problem.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;For raiders.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The primary issues we're beginning to see is lower end warriors having to follow a specific path for weaponry/aggro progression, and that progression being simply unavailable for non raiding warriors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At this point, we're beginning to see Qvic-Txevu level drops in single group content for OTW's (Other than warriors).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Missing within the itemization schemata at this level are:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1. Hate focus:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It's on the Time BP, and the Qvic gloves, both content that single group play has passed for OTW's, but there's nothing for warriors in non-raid content with a hate focus.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2. Imbued Click:&amp;nbsp; Symbol of the Planemasters (Time) ... Call of Fire Gloves (VT)... both content that single group OTW gear has surpassed significantly, nothing currently known to be available as an alternative to non raiders.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3. Weaponry:&amp;nbsp; Single group weaponry is lagging terribly behind other gear.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; There is no alternative to Darkblade, Fleshbiter (Content which single group OTW gear has passed), nor is there any reasonable Qvic/Inktu'Ta/Txevu level weaponry like other gear.&amp;nbsp; Weaponry available to single group players in EQ is really falling way behind, and warrior oriented weaponry is terrible.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;4. Armor Class:&amp;nbsp; Gear in the last few expansions has been woefully inadequate in AC, and that trend appears to continue in TSS at all areas of play, but in particular in single group level of play.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; There are simply put, too many high HP/Low AC items entering the game at the low level and not a counterbalancing level of even decent AC items entering the world in the single group game.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
