      <title>Weekly Question:  Week of October 9th</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=26049#M26049</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Warrior question:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Historically, resurrection effects never depleted Endurance, only putting on items with END and stats gave more "empty" potential endurance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; With TSS, this has changed, and we now have a completely empty endurance pool on resurrection, which really limits what we are able to do in a post res environment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; This actually represents a dramatic change from all precedent, when since Kunark throughout the rest of the game, we've been able to use at least one discipline on resurrection.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Now with the ooc regen system, we've got a minimum cooldown time of until reseffects wear to generate enough END to cover the use of even one disc, and that's not counting any AE's that are occurring.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We do not have the ability to improve regen outside of the ooc regen system such as C7, or bard songs, etc.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We would like to be returned to the state we have had since the implementation of the END system, which is to be resurrected in with a minimum level of Endurance.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2006 08:34:20 GMT</pubDate>
