    <item>
      <title>Suggested Improvements for Mid-level Warriors</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=26002#M26002</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;While dramatic improvements to the damage output of other classes tends to occur at higher levels and/or with access to PoTime+ raid gear, lower level Warriors need competative aggro and some passive survivability advantage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I realize that the addition of "-1 DI", the Sturdyness AA ability, and the Provoke line has helped with both of these issues. Nonetheless, some modest improvents to mid-level Warriors seems to me to be potentially helpful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Mock/Scowls Line&lt;br&gt;Unlinking Mock/Scowls and Bazu has made 2Hders and sword and board more practical for 70+ Warriors at the cost of expending Endurance. I suggest adding Rude Gesture to the Mock/Scowls line to accomplish the same for mid-level Warirors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Rude Gesture&lt;br&gt;Level 56&lt;br&gt;600 Hate&lt;br&gt;300 Endurance&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. Right Click Weapon Buffs&lt;br&gt;Glove of the Crimson Sigil and Symbol of the Plansmasters are acquireable only in raids. New upgraded versions should have been provided from time to time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;While mid-level non-raiding Warriors can be buffed with Trickster's, I can see no reason that a a right click weapon aggro buff isn't provided for mid-level non-raiding Warirors on an item that can be obtained in appropriate non-raid content. Something like:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Level 56&lt;br&gt;Decrease hitpoints by 50-75&lt;br&gt;Stun 1.0&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3. Shield Specialist&lt;br&gt;The loss of ~30% of a Warrior's DPS when switching from DW to sword and board is the case for mid-level Warriros as well. True, ~100AC not subject to the softcap is potentially a great benefit to them, but they are just a much as any Wariror forced to use a weapon designed to be use two at a time on it's own with a shield.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Shield Specialist should made available to Warriors level 56 and above.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I realize these suggestions might be contentious. My intention is only to trickle down capabilities provided to 70+ Warirors to mid-level Warriors who face many of the same issues - not to provide them with unbalanced advantage vs. their competition for group spots - merely to balance the scales a bit better and make 2Handers and sword and board more practical for mid-level Warriors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;10-06-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;04:24 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
