      <title>Newest Warrior Question:  9-6-06</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=25493#M25493</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Warrior question:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Many of our skills and AA's are not usable while performing our primary function, because of the way we're set up insofar as "casting times" is concerned.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;All of the Veteran Reward AA's, as well as Aura of the Champion/Myrmidon have "cast times", but due to a lack of actual channelling, or the inability of the concentration AA&amp;nbsp; to affect these, a single hit for a single point of damage causes an automatic interruption of those skills.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Many warriors feel that since pretty much all other classes, outside of special circumstances, can utilize all of their skills as well as the veteran AA's while performing their primary function, we should be able to as well.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Can either the skills themselves be adjusted, or have the concentration AA apply to them so that we can use these while taking damage?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
